name: Walla Walla County HD- COVID Provider
notes:
**THIS CLINIC IS BY APPOINTMENT ONLY FOR 1st DOSE PFIZER VACCINATIONS for all qualifying individuals aged 12 years & over. Parental/Guardian consent is required for 12 – 17 year olds, parent/guardian consent and signature can be completed on-site or in the final screen of the online registration process. Janssen (Johnson & Johnson) vaccine is also available for people 18 years and older. This clinic is at the Providence Southgate Medical Park main building (the former Walla Walla General Hospital) 1025 South 2nd Ave. Participants are advised to stay to their right as they enter the campus and proceed to the main entrance, instead of going to Urgent Care. COVID vaccine is not available in Urgent Care.
Masks are required. If you do not have a mask, one will be provided.
We look forward to seeing you. Thanks for keeping Walla Walla well.

** ESTA CLÍNICA ES CON CITA SOLAMENTE PARA LAS VACUNAS DE LA PRIMERA DOSIS DE PFIZER para personas calificadas de 12 años en Adelante.  Se requiere el consentimiento de los padres / tutores para los jóvenes de 12 - 17 años, las firmas y el consentimiento en la pantalla de registro final.** Esto será en el edificio principal de Providence Southgate Medical Park, (antes conocido como el Hospital General de Walla Walla)1025 Sur 2nd ave.  Se recomienda a los participantes que se mantengan a su derecha al ingresar y que se dirijan a la entrada principal, en lugar de ir a Atención de Urgencia.  La Vacuna COVID no está disponible en Atención de Urgencias. **
El cubre bocas es requerido. Si no tiene un cubre bocas, se le proporcionará una.  
Esperamos verlo. Gracias por cuidar a Walla Walla.
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Rebel Med NW - COVID Vaccine Clinic
notes:
***We will accept both first and second dose appointments*** ***Please notify us of a cancelation ASAP, we have patients on waiting list, and would prefer not to waste vaccines*** You must provide insurance (photo ID if you do not have insurance) by one of the 2 methods below before you check-in for vaccine. Upload options 1. Prepmod at time of sign up 2. bring your insurance card to your visit. We are administering the first/second dose of the Moderna vaccine. Moderna is currently approved for all adults 18 years and older. Please bring a face covering that covers the mouth and nose. Everyone is required to stay 15-30 minutes under observation after receiving the vaccine. 
****Rebel Med NW is located on the 2nd floor, with the entrance on NW Vernon Place. Across the street from the Olympic Athletic Club. We are an integrative medical clinic specializing in Naturopathic Primary Care, Acupuncture, and Mind Body Medicine. Please be respectful of the space as treatments may be ongoing. Please contact 206-297-6013, and ask to speak to a provider on call if you have a question, leave a voicemail and we will return as soon as we are available. Call 911 if life-threatening emergency, and you are in need of immediate help.
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Clark County PH- COVID Vaccine Site

address.street1: Yacolt Fire Station Admin Building 300 West Hoag Street

notes:
The Yacolt Fire Station vaccination site is providing the Johnson & Johnson vaccine and the Pfizer vaccine. The Johnson & Johnson vaccine requires only one dose; you will not need to return for a second dose. The Pfizer vaccine requires two doses; if this is your first dose, you will need to return for a second dose.

Please do not arrive more than 10 minutes before your scheduled appointment. Arriving too early can lead to longer waiting times. 

You will be asked to remain at the vaccination site for 15 to 30 minutes after being vaccinated. Medical personnel will be monitoring you for possible reactions. Severe reactions are rare. 

What to bring:
•	Identification: If you have identification or some other proof of your date of birth, please bring it. This helps to ensure registration information is accurate. But ID is not required for vaccination. 
•	Face covering: Face coverings must be worn while at the COVID-19 vaccination site. 
•	Please wear a short-sleeved shirt or shirt with loose sleeves that can be pulled up. You will receive your COVID-19 vaccine in your upper arm. 

El sitio de vacunación de la estación de bomberos de Yacolt está proporcionando la vacuna Johnson & Johnson y la vacuna Pfizer. La vacuna de Johnson & Johnson requiere solo una dosis; no necesitará regresar para una segunda dosis. La vacuna Pfizer requiere dos dosis; si esta es su primera dosis, deberá regresar para una segunda dosis.

Por favor, no llegue más de 10 minutos antes de su cita. Llegar con demasiada antelación puede causar tiempos de espera más largos.

Se le pedirá que permanezca en el centro de vacunación de 15 a 30 minutos después de ser vacunado. El personal médico le vigilará para detectar posibles reacciones. Las reacciones graves son poco frecuentes.  

Qué debe traer:
•	Identificación: Si tiene un documento de identitificación, o documento con fecha de nacimiento, por favor tráigalo. Esto ayuda a asegurar que la información de registro es correcta. Pero no es necesario presentar un documento de identidad para la vacunación.  
•	Prenda para cubrirse la cara: Debe llevar una prenda para cubrirse la cara mientras esté en el centro de vacunación de COVID-19.  
•	Por favor, lleve una camisa de mangas cortas o una camisa con mangas sueltas que se puedan subir. Usted recibirá la vacuna contra la COVID-19 en la parte superior del brazo.
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.
